  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Warehouse Assistant",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities: </p><p>1. Warehouse Operations </p><p>Assist in receiving, inspecting, and verifying incoming goods against purchase orders. </p><p>Properly store materials and products in designated warehouse locations. </p><p>Pick, pack, and prepare orders for shipment based on customer or internal requirements. </p><p>Load and unload goods safely using the appropriate equipment (e.g., forklifts, pallet jacks). </p><p>2. Inventory Management </p><p>Conduct regular stock checks and cycle counts to maintain inventory accuracy. </p><p>Update inventory records using manual logs. </p><p>Identify and report discrepancies, damages, or shortages in stock. </p><p>3. Logistics & Coordination </p><p>Assist in coordinating with drivers and logistics teams for timely delivery of goods. </p><p>Ensure proper labeling, documentation, and tracking of shipments. </p><p>Support returns and exchanges by following company procedures. </p><p>4. Compliance & Safety </p><p>Follow all warehouse safety protocols and procedures to prevent accidents. </p><p>Maintain cleanliness and organization in the warehouse. </p><p>Adhere to company policies and regulatory standards related to warehouse operations. </p><p>5. Equipment Handling & Maintenance </p><p>Operate warehouse equipment safely and report any malfunctions. </p><p>Assist in routine maintenance and upkeep of warehouse tools and storage areas. </p><p>6. Work Environment: </p><p>Cold storage warehouse, temperatures as low as -18°C. </p><p>Protective clothing and equipment (e.g., insulated gloves, jackets, boots) will be provided to ensure comfort and safety while working in cold conditions. <br /></p><p>Requirements: </p><p>Secondary school education or a relevant certificate in logistics, warehousing, or supply chain. </p><p>At least 1 year of experience in warehouse or logistics operations. </p><p>Ability to lift and move heavy goods (if required). </p><p>Forklift certification (preferred but not required). </p><p>Strong teamwork and organizational skills. </p><p>Ability to work in extreme temperatures, down to -18°C, while adhering to health and safety protocols. </p>",
